# Raspberry Pi MITM Proxy Project

This project sets up a Man-in-the-Middle (MITM) proxy on a Raspberry Pi using `mitmproxy`, `Apache`, `iptables`, and `hostapd` to intercept and monitor HTTP traffic on a Wi-Fi network.

## Prerequisites

- Raspberry Pi
- Raspbian OS installed
- Internet access

## Features

- MITM Proxy using `mitmproxy`
- Apache web server for serving certificates
- Hostapd for Wi-Fi access point
- DHCP and DNS configuration
- IPTables for traffic redirection
